CRIMEAN-CONGO HEMORRHAGIC FEVER - INDIA: (GUJARAT)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 27 Jul 2017 04:00 AM IST
Source: Times of India [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/rajkot/jasdan-man-tests-positive-for-cchf-virus/articleshow/59777430.cms


A 50-year-old man from Jasdan taluka of Rajkot has tested positive for Crimean-Congo haemorrhagic fever (CCHF) virus.

Rajkot chief district health officer (CDHO) Dr V H Pathak said that the man had come to the Rajkot civil hospital on [Fri 21 Jul 2017] from Shivrajpur village of Jasdan with high fever. ."His samples were sent for testing for diseases including CCHF virus." Pathak said that the test results, which arrived on [Tue 25 Jul 2017] evening, stated that he was positive for CCHF virus.

This is 1st case of the dreaded CCHF this year [2017] in Rajkot. Last year [2016] also, CCHF case was reported from Jasdan taluka of the district.

